Package coins.ir.hir

Interface Summary
AsmStmt The C front of COINS accepts following asm statement: asm("#param paramDecsriptionList \n" "#clobber destroyed-register-list \n" asmInstructionSequence , actual-parameter-list ); where paramDescriptionList -> paramDescription | paramDescriptionList , paramDescription paramDescription -> %register // input parameter variable (rvalue) | w%register // output parameter variable (lvalue) | m%register // input/output parameter variable (lvalue) | s // constant representing static address | a // constant repreZsenting automatic variable address destroyed-register-list -> %register // register contents is destroyed | destroyed-register-list , %register asmInstructionSequence -> "asmInstruction \n" | asmInstructionSequence "asmInstruction \n" actualParameterList -> expression // expression representing actual parameter | actualParameterList , expression The %register represents a register or a class of registers defined in the TMD.
